Ex.No: 5

INSTALLATION OF ROOTKITS AND USING VARIOUS OPTIONS
Date:


AIM

To install and use the rootkit tool in Kali Linux to detect rootkits and unauthorized access attempts using standard security tools such as chkrootkit, rkhunter, and Lynis

ALGORITHM

Step 1: Start Kali Linux in VMware
Step 2: Install and run the Chkrootkit, tool to initiate a scan for potential rootkits present in the system.
Step 3: Verify the successful execution of Chkrootkit and check whether any rootkits have been detected in the system
Step 4: Install and Update rkhunter tool that reports file integrity status, hidden files, suspicious kernel modules, and configuration warnings.
Step 5: Install Lynis tool and run lynis security audit that generates a detailed system audit report highlighting potential security weaknesses and malware indicators.
Step 6: Stop the execution

PROGRAM CODING ROOTKIT COMMANDS:
chrootkit:
Download chkrootkit source code cd /opt
sudo wget ftp://ftp.chkrootkit.org/pub/seg/pac/chkrootkit.tar.gz

Extract the tar file
sudo tar -xvzf chkrootkit.tar.gz

Move into the directory 
cd chkrootkit-*
Run chkrootkit (IMPORTANT) 
sudo ./chkrootkit

rkhunter

Install required dependencies 
sudo apt update
sudo apt install wget perl -y
Download rkhunter source
cd /opt
sudo wget https://downloads.sourceforge.net/project/rkhunter/rkhunter/1.4.6/rkhunter-1.4.6.tar.gz
Extract the archive
sudo tar -xvzf rkhunter-1.4.6.tar.gz
cd rkhunter-1.4.6

Install rkhunter manually 
sudo ./installer.sh --install
Update database
sudo rkhunter --update
Initialize baseline
sudo rkhunter --propupd

Run scan
sudo rkhunter --check
